The “I Support Black Women” campaign aims to amplify and capture Black Women leaders of all identities (Transgender, Immigrant, Disabled, Fat, Queer, Working-Class) to share their work and why they have dedicated their life to social change. The campaign also supports a fundraiser to open a physical location for the @schoolforblackfeministpolitics (SBFP), a Black feminist political education initiative and hub.
